# Testing

## Test types

- Unit/integration (Vitest)
  - Config: app/vitest.config.ts, .coverage.ts, .setup.ts, .resolve-aliases.ts
  - Run all: pnpm test
  - Coverage: pnpm test:coverage (LCOV produced for Sonar)
  - Generate Prisma client before tests that import it: pnpm --filter dineros-app exec prisma generate
- Forecast engine suites
  - Runner: app/server/services/forecast/__tests__/test-runner.ts (tsx)
  - Commands: test:forecast, test:forecast:unit, :integration, :all, :performance
  - Large collection of unit/integration/regression tests under forecast/__tests__
- API/server tests
  - app/server/api/__tests__/* cover endpoints and regressions
  - app/server/lib/**/__tests__ and app/server/services/**/__tests__ for utility/service logic
- App libs
  - app/lib/__tests__/* cover shared utilities (rounding, sorting, date helpers, table filtering)
- E2E (Playwright)
  - app/tests/e2e/specs/public/* and specs/authed/* with visual snapshots
  - Run: pnpm test:e2e (chromium public+authed), update snapshots locally or via staging workflow

## Writing tests

- Co-locate under the nearest __tests__ directory mirroring feature path
- Prefer deterministic data; many tests mock external services
- Use TZ=UTC when dealing with dates/times
- For endpoints, assert both success and error paths (authz, validation)
- For forecast, prefer adding minimal reproduction fixtures and include snapshots where applicable (existing patterns under __tests__/__snapshots__)

## CI behavior

- PRs run lint, unit/integration, pre-commit security, and CodeQL
- Same-repo PRs also build and deploy to staging; health verification runs after rollout
- E2E visual snapshots against staging are manual (separate workflow)
